{
  "stem": "20609.1",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We landed in Nyborg, and we were assigned to a-- to a family, right?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And again, [LAUGHS] we were supposed to get schooling, right?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then we were told once a week in the afternoon from 1 o'clock till 5 o'clock, we had a teacher.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he was going to give us schooling, right?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "In the meantime, the minute we got to this farmer, we got up at 6 o'clock in the morning milking cows and doing all the things we never-- believe it or not, there was nights when I cried like a baby because I looked at my hands and it was-- I thought, especially, it was so cold that time.",
      "word_count": 59
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I wasn't used to that kind of thing.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "After all, 13 years-- what do you expect, right?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And so this once a week, we were looking forward to.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I had a bicycle.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They got-- we got a bicycle.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And-- and, by the way, we never get paid.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We weren't supposed to get paid.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "That was the deal.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But we figured out that's-- you know, you get used to it.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "You know, it was like we were safe.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And two months later, April 9, the Germans marched into Denmark.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So they were following me again.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So being on a farm away from the cities, we never saw any German soldiers.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But we knew they were there because all of a sudden, all products-- you know, like pigs and milk and cheese-- was now delivered to actually to the German government because-- which, to them, Denmark was a heaven because all of a sudden all that export now was going-- It got so bad that the--the--the kids in the cities were-- were-- the people in the cities were highly rationed.",
      "word_count": 69
    }
  ],
